<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi><note><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi> is added on the pilaster.</note> <g type="kaḻañcu"/> matirai koṇṭak kopparakecaripanmakki yāṇṭu mu {built over}
<lb n="2"/>Eṭṭā Āvatu kuṉṟakūṟṟattu Avanikaṉtaṟpa ˚<hi rend="grantha">īśvagṛha</hi>ttu {built over}
<lb n="3"/>ṭai Ittaḷi vaṇṇa {unfinished}
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the [thirty-eight] year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken Madurai. <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gṛhattu</foreign></supplied> of the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>īśvara</foreign></supplied> [of] Avanikaṉtaṟpa (i.e. Kaṉtaṟpa upon earth), a <foreign>devadāna</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> the checking of coins and gold (<foreign>vaṇṇa</foreign> for unfinished <foreign>vaṇṇakku</foreign>?) of this temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittaḷi</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> </p></div>

